msgstr "Orixe"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/02.what_is_yunohost/index.mdx:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "YunoHost was created in February 2012 after something like this:\n"
msgstr "YunoHost creouse en Febreiro de 2012 despois dalgo semellante a isto:\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/02.what_is_yunohost/index.mdx:33
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"> \"Shit, I'm too lazy to reconfigure my mail server... Beudbeud, how were you able to get your little server running with LDAP?\"\n"
"> <small>*Kload, February 2012*</small>\n"
msgstr ""
"> \"Merda, malditas as gañas de reconfigurar o correo electrónico... Beudbeud, como fixeches para que funcionase o teu pequeno servidor con LDAP?\"\n"
"> <small>*Kload, February 2012*</small>\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/02.what_is_yunohost/index.mdx:35
#, no-wrap
msgid "All that was needed was an admin interface for Beudbeud's server to make something usable, so Kload decided to develop one. Finally, after automating several configs and packaging in some web apps, YunoHost v1 was finished.\n"
msgstr "Todo o que facía falta era unha interface web para o servidor de Beudbeud para ter algo usable, así que Kload decideu crear unha. Finalmente, despois de automatizar certas configuración e empaquetar algunhas aplicacións web, YunoHost v1 naceu.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/02.what_is_yunohost/index.mdx:37
#, no-wrap
msgid "Noting the growing enthusiasm around YunoHost and around self-hosting in general, the original developers along with new contributors decided to start work on version 2, a more extensible, more powerful, more easy-to-use, and at that, one that makes a nice cup of fair-trade coffee for the elves of Lapland.\n"
msgstr "Vendo o entusiasmo con que foi acollida YunoHost e a auto-hospedaxe en xeral, as desenvolvedoras orixinais xunto coas novas persoas colaboradoras decidiron comezar a traballar na versión 2, máis ampliable, más robusta e aínda máis fácil de usar, e así converterse nun bo café de comerzo xusto para os elfos da Laponia.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/02.what_is_yunohost/index.mdx:39
#, no-wrap
msgid "The name **YunoHost** comes from the jargon \"[Y U NO](https://knowyourmeme.com/memes/y-u-no-guy) Host\". The [Internet meme](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet_meme) should illustrate it:\n"
msgstr "O nome **YunoHost** vén da expresión en xerga \"[Y U NO](https://knowyourmeme.com/memes/y-u-no-guy) Host\". O [meme de Internet](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet_meme) debería ilustralo:\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/02.what_is_yunohost/index.mdx:42
#, no-wrap
msgid "![The meme in question, showing a guy with a face bent in frustration and questioning \"Y U NO Host\"](/img/dude_yunohost.jpg)\n"
msgstr "![o meme citado, mostrando un tipo coa cara baixa en xesto de frustación e preguntándose \"Y U NO Host\"](/img/dude_yunohost.jpg)\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: docs/admin/02.what_is_yunohost/index.mdx:44
#, no-wrap
msgid "What YunoHost is not?"
msgstr "Que non é YunoHost?"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/02.what_is_yunohost/index.mdx:47
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "YunoHost is *not* an enterprise or a for-profit entity. It is developed and maintained by volunteers. We do not sell services, we do not host or control your data or services in any way, and we have no intention or interest in monetizing anything. We also do not offer any formal guarantees. Our goal is simply to develop and maintain YunoHost in the hope that it contributes to a more decentralized internet and empowers people to reclaim autonomy over their digital services and technology. That said, we do our best to provide community support, and commercial support may be available through third parties if needed.\n"
msgid "**YunoHost is *not* an enterprise or a for-profit entity.** It is developed and maintained by volunteers. We do not sell services, we do not host or control your data or services in any way, and we have no intention or interest in monetizing anything. We also do not offer any formal guarantees. Our goal is simply to develop and maintain YunoHost in the hope that it contributes to a more decentralized internet and empowers people to reclaim autonomy over their digital services and technology. That said, we do our best to provide community support, and commercial support may be available through third parties if needed.\n"
msgstr "YunoHost *non* é unha empresa ou unha organización en busca de lucro. Desenvólvese e mantense grazas ás persoas voluntarias. Non vendemos servizos, nin hospedamos nin controlamos os teus datos ou servizos en ningunha forma, e non temos intención nin interese en facer cartos con nada. Tampouco ofrecemos ningún tipo de garantía formal. O noso obxectivo é simplemente desenvolver e manter YunoHost coa esperanza de que contribúa a unha internet descentralizada que empodere ás persoas a reclamar autonomía sobre os servizos dixitais e tecnoloxías. Dito isto, facemos o que podemos para proporcionar axuda á comunidade, e podes obter axuda comercial desde terceiras partes se o precisases.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/02.what_is_yunohost/index.mdx:49
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "YunoHost as a project is *not* apolitical. By its very nature, YunoHost promotes a decentralized internet and technologies that empower people. We reject the flawed notion that technology is inherently neutral, or that software projects should remain neutral. Many contributors to the project remain vigilant about the social and political implications of technological developments, and emphasize the importance of solidarity and alignment with broader movements such as feminism, LGBTQIA+ rights and visibility, environmental justice and social justice. We stand firmly against fascism, sexism, racism, xenophobia, [bigotry](https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bigotry), ableism, imperialism, extractivism, [eugenics](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eugenics), and right-wing libertarianism. If you are not aligned with these values, you are encouraged to *not* use YunoHost and look for a different system.\n"
msgid "**YunoHost as a project is *not* apolitical.** By its very nature, YunoHost promotes a decentralized internet and technologies that empower people. We reject the flawed notion that technology is inherently neutral, or that software projects should remain neutral. Many contributors to the project remain vigilant about the social and political implications of technological developments, and emphasize the importance of solidarity and alignment with broader movements such as feminism, LGBTQIA+ rights and visibility, environmental justice and social justice. We stand firmly against fascism, sexism, racism, xenophobia, [bigotry](https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bigotry), ableism, imperialism, extractivism, [eugenics](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eugenics), and right-wing libertarianism. If you are not aligned with these values, you are encouraged to *not* use YunoHost and look for a different system.\n"
msgstr "YunoHost *non* é un proxecto apolítico. Pola súa natureza, YunoHost promove unha internet e tecnoloxías descentralizadas que empoderen ás persoas. Rexeitamos ese concepto ruín que di que a tecnoloxía é neutra por natureza, ou que os proxectos de software deberían permanecer neutrais. Moitas colaboradoras do proxecto permanecen vixiantes sobre as implicacións políticas e sociais dos desenvolvementos tecnolóxicos, e salientan a importancia da solidaridade e moverse xunto a movementos máis amplos como o feminismo, visibilidade e dereitos LGBTQIA+, xustiza ambiental e social. Mostrámonos firmes en contra do fascismo, sexismo, racismo, xenofobia, [intolerancia](https://gl.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intolerancia), capacitismo, imperialismo, extractivismo, [euxenesia](https://es.wiktionary.org/wiki/eugenesia), e os libertarios de dereitas. Se non te representan estes valores, considera *non* utilizar YunoHost e buscar unha alternativa diferente.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/02.what_is_yunohost/index.mdx:51
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "YunoHost is *not* designed to \"scale\" in the traditional sense. It is intended for a relatively modest number of user accounts and simultaneous users. While there is no strict limit—since performance depends heavily on your specific setup — , we estimate that some technical adjustments may be necessary when reaching 250~500 user accounts, or about 50 simultaneous users on resource-intensive apps. That said, YunoHost can comfortably handle hosting a website or several lightweight services, even with thousands of daily visitors.\n"
msgid "**YunoHost is *not* designed to \"scale\" in the traditional sense.** It is intended for a relatively modest number of user accounts and simultaneous users. While there is no strict limit—since performance depends heavily on your specific setup — , we estimate that some technical adjustments may be necessary when reaching 250~500 user accounts, or about 50 simultaneous users on resource-intensive apps. That said, YunoHost can comfortably handle hosting a website or several lightweight services, even with thousands of daily visitors.\n"
msgstr "YunoHost *non* se deseñou para \"escalar\", no sentido tradicional. O seu propósito é ter un número relativamente modesto de contas de persoas usuarias e usuarias simultáneas. Aínda que non hai un límite estrito establecido ―xa que o rendemento depende da túa configuración concreta―, estimamos que farían falla algúns axustes técnicos ao acadar entre 250 e 500 contas de usuarias, ou ter unhas 50 usuarias usando simultáneamente as aplicacións que consumen moitos recursos. Dito isto, YunoHost pode comodamente hospedar un sitio web ou varios servizos lixeiros, incluso con miles de visitas diarias.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/02.what_is_yunohost/index.mdx:53
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "YunoHost is primarily designed for people who want things to \"just work\". Of course, it’s not perfect — we're constantly working to improve the user experience, robustness, and simplicity. Though YunoHost is \"tinkerable\", the first target public is *not* power users with complex or highly customized use cases in mind. We encourage you to keep your setup as simple as possible. That said, you are than welcome to experiment and share your feedback with us!\n"
msgid "**YunoHost is primarily designed for people who want things to \"just work\".** Of course, it’s not perfect — we're constantly working to improve the user experience, robustness, and simplicity. Though YunoHost is \"tinkerable\", the first target public is *not* power users with complex or highly customized use cases in mind. We encourage you to keep your setup as simple as possible. That said, you are than welcome to experiment and share your feedback with us!\n"
msgstr "YunoHost deseñouse principalmente para persoas que queren que as cousas \"simplemente funcionen\". Por suposto, non é perfecta ―traballamos constantemente para mellorar a experiencia das usuarias, a súa resistencia e simplicidade. Aínda que se pode \"chafullar\" en YunoHost, o público obxectivo principal *non* son as usuarias experimentadas que teñen en mente casos complexos e altamente personalizables. Recomendámosche manter a configuración o máis simple posible. Dito isto, animámoste a experimentar e compartir a túa experiencia con nós!\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/02.what_is_yunohost/index.mdx:55
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "YunoHost is *not* designed to be a *heavy* multi-tenant solution for providing services to completely separate organizations across different domains. While you *can* manage multiple domains and subdomains — such as hosting apps for friends, colleagues, an association — you should keep in mind that there is no strict isolation between apps. Under the hood, all applications share the same system and environment.\n"
msgid "**YunoHost is *not* designed to be a *heavy* multi-tenant solution** for providing services to completely separate organizations across different domains. While you *can* manage multiple domains and subdomains — such as hosting apps for friends, colleagues, an association — you should keep in mind that there is no strict isolation between apps. Under the hood, all applications share the same system and environment.\n"
msgstr "YunoHost *non* se deseñou para ser unha solución *pesada* multipropósito para proporcionar servizos para organizacións completamente separadas usando múltiples dominios. Aínda que *podes* xestionar varios domios e subdominios ―como hospedar aplicacións para as amizades, colegas, unha asociación― deberías ter presente que non hai un illamento estrito entre as aplicacións. Por dentro, todas as aplicacións comparten o mesmo sistema e entorno.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/02.what_is_yunohost/index.mdx:57
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "(Note for power users) YunoHost does not use \"hard\" containerization technologies such as Docker for its apps. This is partly for historical reasons, but also to keep the system lightweight — both in terms of resource usage and technical complexity. That said, we do take security seriously: applications run under dedicated user accounts with limited privileges and capabilities, and we're continuously working to enhance the system’s security.\n"
msgid "(Note for power users) **YunoHost does not use \"hard\" containerization technologies** such as Docker for its apps. This is partly for historical reasons, but also to keep the system lightweight — both in terms of resource usage and technical complexity. That said, we do take security seriously: applications run under dedicated user accounts with limited privileges and capabilities, and we're continuously working to enhance the system’s security.\n"
msgstr "(Nota para usuarias experimentadas) YunoHost non usa teconoloxías \"hard containerization\" como Docker para as súas apps. En parte débese a razóns históricas, pero tamén para manter a lixeireza do sistema ―en termos de uso de recursos e complexidade técnica. Dito isto, somos serias respecto da seguridade: as aplicacións funcionan baixo contas de usuaria dedicadas con privilexios e capacidades limitadas, e traballamos de xeito contínuo para mellorar a seguridade do sistema.\n"

